1. Create maven web project
2. Inside src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/web.xml
	create a servelate with any name ex: springrest1
3  Create xml file with name  servlat name+servlet.xml :   ex springrest1-servlat.xml
	inside this file you can define your bean or you can import some other bean configuration xml file
	
	
	
	Note: main spring configuration file should be servletName-servlet.xml
	
	In this example you can get annotation based configuration
	
	for annotation based configuration:
		create a class, annotate with @Configuration, then define your all the beans inside this class
		
		Also you can import other bean configuration file in this main configuration file.
		 